    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-03-03T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-03-01T00:14:00-05:00" n="417"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d417">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 322.112J72.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">
                        <gloss type="from">American Citizens at Guayaquil</gloss> to the <gloss
                            type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Guayaquil</hi>
                        </placeName>, [<date ana="#date_undated-inferred-from-document-content"
                            calendar="gregorian" notAfter="1914-03-03T23:59:59-05:00"
                            notBefore="1914-03-01T00:00:00-05:14">
                            <hi rend="italic">undated</hi>
                        </date>
                        <hi rend="italic">; received March 3, 1914</hi>]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Jones, ex-Consul Guayaquil, imprisoned since December 17th without hope release.
                    Every attorney consulted considers extremely unlawful and groundless. We
                    American citizens request immediate protection. Consul Coding familiar with
                    case.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Yoder et al</hi>
                    </signed>.</closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
